cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the formalism and semantics of first-order logic and its application in logical/relational database systems, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Databases (cs.DB), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Programming Languages (cs.PL). However, since the paper focuses more on the formalism and semantics of first-order logic, cs.LO is the most likely category, followed by cs.DB and cs.AI. The paper also mentions the conceptual structures approach, which is related to formal concept analysis, and information flow, which could be relevant to cs.PL and cs.SE.
